<lb />3) mischance, misfortune: <cit><quote>forced by need and a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 92</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>dismay not at this a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>by some unlooked for a. cut off,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.214" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 214</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this a. is not unlike my dream,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 143</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>moving --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.135" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 135</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the shot of a. nor dart of chance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.278" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 278</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all solemn things should answer solemn --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.192" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 192</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with mortal --s opprest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.99" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 99</bibl></cit>.
